<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>New on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/new/</link><description>Recent content in New on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/new/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_alloc — Memory Allocation Failed Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-alloc-3/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-alloc-3/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_alloc--memory-allocation-failed-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_alloc — Memory Allocation Failed Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_alloc&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when the &lt;code&gt;new&lt;/code&gt; operator or &lt;code&gt;malloc()&lt;/code&gt; fails to allocate the requested amount of memory. This typically happens when the system runs out of available memory, the requested size is unreasonably large, or there is a memory leak gradually exhausting available resources. The exception is defined in &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;new&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requesting an excessively large allocation&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;new int[10000000000]&lt;/code&gt; exceeds available memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Memory leak accumulation&lt;/strong&gt; — repeated allocations without deallocation exhaust memory over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fragmented heap&lt;/strong&gt; — total free memory exists but is not contiguous&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Too many threads&lt;/strong&gt; — each thread&amp;rsquo;s stack consumes memory, reducing heap availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-stdnothrow-to-avoid-exceptions"&gt;Fix 1: Use std::nothrow to avoid exceptions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;new&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; arr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;nothrow) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100000000&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (arr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nullptr&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Allocation failed — out of memory&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* use arr ... */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;delete&lt;/span&gt;[] arr;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-catch-and-handle-bad_alloc"&gt;Fix 2: Catch and handle bad_alloc&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;new&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;vector&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;vector&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; v;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; v.resize(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000000000ULL&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may throw std::bad_alloc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;bad_alloc&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Memory allocation failed: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.what() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-validate-size-before-allocating"&gt;Fix 3: Validate size before allocating&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;new&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;limits&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;template&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;typename&lt;/span&gt; T&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;T&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; safe_allocate(size_t count) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (count &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;numeric_limits&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;size_t&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;::&lt;/span&gt;max() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;sizeof&lt;/span&gt;(T)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Allocation size would overflow&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nullptr&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;nothrow) T[count];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; safe_allocate&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (p) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Allocated successfully&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;delete&lt;/span&gt;[] p;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-memory-pools-for-frequent-small-allocations"&gt;Fix 4: Use memory pools for frequent small allocations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;vector&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;memory&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ObjectPool&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ObjectPool(size_t pool_size) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; pool_(pool_size) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (size_t i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;; i &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; pool_size; i&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;++&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; free_.push_back(i);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;allocate&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (free_.empty()) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; idx &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; free_.back();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; free_.pop_back();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; idx;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;deallocate&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; idx) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; free_.push_back(idx);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;private&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;vector&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; pool_;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;vector&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; free_;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ObjectPool pool(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1000&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; obj &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pool.allocate();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cout &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Allocated object at index &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; obj &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; pool.deallocate(obj);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;new&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* Huge allocation that will likely fail */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; huge &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000000000LL&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;delete&lt;/span&gt;[] huge;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;bad_alloc&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Cannot allocate: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.what() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* Using new(std::nothrow) for safe failure */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt;(std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;nothrow) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000000000LL&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;p) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Allocation returned nullptr&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/length-error-3/"&gt;std::length_error&lt;/a&gt; — container resize exceeds max allowed size&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-allocation-length-2/"&gt;std::bad_array_length&lt;/a&gt; — invalid array length in new[]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/memory-leak/"&gt;Memory Leak: Valgrind Lost Bytes&lt;/a&gt; — gradual memory exhaustion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_alloc — Memory Allocation Failure Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/allocator-failed/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/allocator-failed/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_alloc--memory-allocation-failure-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_alloc — Memory Allocation Failure Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_alloc&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when &lt;code&gt;operator new&lt;/code&gt; fails to allocate the requested memory. This typically happens when the system runs out of memory or the process exceeds its memory limits. All dynamic memory allocations using &lt;code&gt;new&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;new[]&lt;/code&gt;, and containers like &lt;code&gt;std::vector&lt;/code&gt; can throw this exception.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdbad_alloc-occurs"&gt;Why std::bad_alloc Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include requesting more memory than is available, excessive memory fragmentation preventing large contiguous allocations, memory leaks exhausting available memory, and process memory limits being reached.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_array_new_length — Array Size Validation Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-allocation-length-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-allocation-length-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_array_new_length--array-size-validation-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_array_new_length — Array Size Validation Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_array_new_length&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you attempt to allocate an array using &lt;code&gt;new[]&lt;/code&gt; with an invalid size — such as a negative number, zero (for some types), or a size that causes internal arithmetic overflow. This exception inherits from &lt;code&gt;std::bad_alloc&lt;/code&gt; and was introduced in C++11.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdbad_array_new_length-occurs"&gt;Why std::bad_array_new_length Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include passing a negative value (converted to a large unsigned) to &lt;code&gt;new[]&lt;/code&gt;, requesting &lt;code&gt;new T[0]&lt;/code&gt; for non-default-constructible types, and size overflow when multiplying element count by element size.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] TypeScript TS2351 — This Expression Is Not Constructable</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2351/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2351/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ts2351--this-expression-is-not-constructable"&gt;TS2351 — This expression is not constructable&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TS2351 occurs when you try to use &lt;code&gt;new&lt;/code&gt; on a value whose type doesn&amp;rsquo;t have a construct signature. This happens when calling &lt;code&gt;new&lt;/code&gt; on a function that isn&amp;rsquo;t a constructor, an object, or a primitive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Using &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; on a regular function
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`Hello, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351: not constructable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Using &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; on an arrow function
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; () &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; ({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Using &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; on a module default export that isn&amp;#39;t a class
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;utils&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;./utils&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;u&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;utils&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Using &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; on an interface
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Factory&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt;()&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Widget&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Factory&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351: interfaces aren&amp;#39;t values
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-a-class-with-a-constructor"&gt;Fix 1: Use a class with a constructor&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — regular function
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Greeter&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Greeter&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — use a class
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Greeter&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;constructor&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Greeter&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// OK
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-factory-function-without-new"&gt;Fix 2: Use factory function without &amp;rsquo;new'&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; () &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; ({ &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — call without &amp;#39;new&amp;#39;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;create&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-import-the-class-correctly"&gt;Fix 3: Import the class correctly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong — importing non-class default export
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;utils&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;./utils&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;utils&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Correct — import a class
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyClass&lt;/span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;./my-class&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;MyClass&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-define-a-construct-signature-for-the-type"&gt;Fix 4: Define a construct signature for the type&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Constructor&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;createInstance&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Ctor&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Constructor&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Ctor&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// OK
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-typescript" data-lang="typescript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Using &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; on a function stored in a variable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;initialize&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; () {};
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;app&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;initialize&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Using &amp;#39;new&amp;#39; on a namespace
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;namespace&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Utils&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;helper() {&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Utils&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// TS2351
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2349/"&gt;TS2349: This expression is not callable&lt;/a&gt; — trying to call &lt;code&gt;()&lt;/code&gt; on non-callable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2688/"&gt;TS2688: Type has no matching call signature&lt;/a&gt; — callable but wrong arguments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/typescript/ts2542/"&gt;TS2542: Cannot read property of type&lt;/a&gt; — property access issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_alloc — Memory Allocation Failed Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/std-bad-alloc/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/std-bad-alloc/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_alloc--memory-allocation-failed-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_alloc — Memory Allocation Failed Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_alloc&lt;/code&gt; exception is thrown when the C++ runtime cannot allocate the requested memory using &lt;code&gt;new&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;new[]&lt;/code&gt;, or &lt;code&gt;std::vector::resize()&lt;/code&gt;. This typically means the system has exhausted its available memory or the process has hit its resource limits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdbad_alloc-occurs"&gt;Why std::bad_alloc Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include allocating very large arrays, requesting more memory than the system has, memory fragmentation on embedded systems, or a combination of small allocations that accumulate over time.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::bad_array_new_length — Invalid Array Allocation Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-allocation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/bad-allocation/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdbad_array_new_length--invalid-array-allocation-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::bad_array_new_length — Invalid Array Allocation Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::bad_array_new_length&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when you attempt to allocate an array with a negative size, zero elements (for types without a non-throwing default constructor in some implementations), or a size that would cause an internal arithmetic overflow. This exception was introduced in C++11 and is a subclass of &lt;code&gt;std::bad_alloc&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdbad_array_new_length-occurs"&gt;Why std::bad_array_new_length Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include requesting &lt;code&gt;new T[negative_number]&lt;/code&gt;, requesting &lt;code&gt;new T[0]&lt;/code&gt; for non-default-constructible types, and size calculations that overflow before the allocation call.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>